The paper discusses the development of information extraction tools for multilingual text analysis, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Specifically, the paper focuses on the recognition of date expressions and geographical place names, which are common tasks in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DL (Deep Learning), as these fields are also relevant to the development of information extraction tools.
